            "nodes": []
          },
          "author": {
            "login": "ConcaveTrillion"
          },
          "body": "Today `scripts/check_dev_local.py` only inspects `uv pip list --format=json`, which doesn't expose the install URL. A fork-pin probe would have to read doctr's `direct_url.json` from dist-info to detect that `python-doctr` came from a contributor's fork rather than `mindee/doctr.git`.\n\nDesign question: which URLs count as `non-canonical`? pyproject already pins doctr from `mindee/doctr.git` so canonical installs leave a `vcs_info` block too. The detector needs a clear rule.\n\nDeferred until a concrete fork-pin workflow needs it; label `status:blocked` until that happens.\n\nSource: docs/ROADMAP.md (dev-local-aware upgrade-deps - Doctr-from-git signal).\nSpec: docs/specs/07-dev-local-upgrade-flow.md\n\n## Acceptance\n- [ ] Decision recorded in 07-dev-local-upgrade-flow.md on which URLs are non-canonical\n- [ ] `check_dev_local.py` reads `direct_url.json` from doctr dist-info\n- [ ] Detector returns dev-local exit code when doctr URL is non-canonical, even with no marker file\n- [ ] Tests cover canonical-URL, fork-URL, and missing-direct_url.json cases\n",
          "closedAt": null,
          "comments": {
            "nodes": []
          },
          "createdAt": "2026-05-10T01:51:51Z",
